defaultDonna defaultLaframboisedefault: Of course not, but the chairman of the IPCC has gone around for years publicly declaring that the entire report is based 100% on peer-reviewed literature. In fact that is not the case. About a third of the sources cited were not peer-reviewed literature and thousands of people who worked on the IPCC report knew that, but none of them talked to the media and none of them protested that the chairman was misrepresenting the process.
